{
  "work_slug": "alices-adventures-in-wonderland-by-lewis-carroll-5",
  "work_title": "Alice's Adventures in Wonderland (version 4)",
  "work_author": "Lewis Carroll",
  "audio_file": "audio-02",
  "audio_url": "https://archive.org/download/alices_adventures_1005_librivox/wonderland_02_carroll.mp3",
  "chapter_title": "02 - The Pool of Tears",
  "reader_name": "Eric Leach",
  "para_gap_threshold": 0.477,
  "page_num": 3,
  "page_total": 3,
  "page_start_sec": 505.02,
  "page_end_sec": 601.04,
  "corrected": "claude",
  "segments": [
    {
      "start": 505.02,
      "end": 507.3,
      "text": "\"We won't talk about her any more if you'd rather not.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 507.94,
      "end": 508.36,
      "text": "\"We, indeed!\"",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 508.68,
      "end": 509.38,
      "text": "cried the Mouse,"
    },
    {
      "start": 509.5,
      "end": 511.7,
      "text": "who was trembling down to the end of his tail."
    },
    {
      "start": 512.56,
      "end": 514.3,
      "text": "\"As if _I_ would talk on such a subject!"
    },
    {
      "start": 514.74,
      "end": 516.7,
      "text": "Our family always _hated_ cats:"
    },
    {
      "start": 516.96,
      "end": 517.52,
      "text": "nasty,"
    },
    {
      "start": 517.6,
      "end": 517.82,
      "text": "low,"
    },
    {
      "start": 517.94,
      "end": 518.74,
      "text": "vulgar things!"
    },
    {
      "start": 519.04,
      "end": 520.4,
      "text": "Don't let me hear the name again!\""
    },
    {
      "start": 520.72,
      "end": 521.74,
      "text": "\"I won't indeed!\""
    },
    {
      "start": 522.02,
      "end": 522.58,
      "text": "said Alice,"
    },
    {
      "start": 522.7,
      "end": 524.78,
      "text": "in a great hurry to change the subject of conversation."
    },
    {
      "start": 526.02,
      "end": 529.64,
      "text": "\"Are you--are you fond--of--of dogs?\" The Mouse did not answer,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 529.72,
      "end": 530.89,
      "text": "so Alice went on eagerly."
    },
    {
      "start": 531.96,
      "end": 533.18,
      "text": "\"There is such a nice little dog near"
    },
    {
      "start": 533.18,
      "end": 534.68,
      "text": "our house, I should like to show you!"
    },
    {
      "start": 534.92,
      "end": 536.28,
      "text": "A little bright-eyed terrier,"
    },
    {
      "start": 536.34,
      "end": 536.64,
      "text": "you know,"
    },
    {
      "start": 536.68,
      "end": 536.86,
      "text": "with,"
    },
    {
      "start": 536.94,
      "end": 537.14,
      "text": "oh,"
    },
    {
      "start": 537.22,
      "end": 539.02,
      "text": "such long curly brown hair!"
    },
    {
      "start": 539.36,
      "end": 540.96,
      "text": "And it'll fetch things when you throw them,"
    },
    {
      "start": 541.02,
      "end": 543.72,
      "text": "and it'll sit up and beg for its dinner, and all sorts of things--"
    },
    {
      "start": 543.86,
      "end": 545.2,
      "text": "I can't remember half of them--"
    },
    {
      "start": 545.78,
      "end": 547.1,
      "text": "and it belongs to a farmer,"
    },
    {
      "start": 547.16,
      "end": 547.46,
      "text": "you know,"
    },
    {
      "start": 547.5,
      "end": 548.94,
      "text": "and he says it's so useful,"
    },
    {
      "start": 549.08,
      "end": 550.32,
      "text": "it's worth a hundred pounds!"
    },
    {
      "start": 551.12,
      "end": 552.78,
      "text": "He says it kills all the rats and--"
    },
    {
      "start": 553.0,
      "end": 553.472,
      "text": "Oh dear!\""
    },
    {
      "start": 553.92,
      "end": 555.56,
      "text": "cried Alice in a sorrowful tone,"
    },
    {
      "start": 555.72,
      "end": 557.36,
      "text": "\"I'm afraid I've offended it again!\""
    },
    {
      "start": 557.58,
      "end": 560.64,
      "text": "For the Mouse was swimming away from her as hard as it could go,"
    },
    {
      "start": 560.72,
      "end": 562.9,
      "text": "and making quite a commotion in the pool as it went."
    },
    {
      "start": 564.04,
      "end": 565.64,
      "text": "So she called softly after it,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 565.66,
      "end": 566.24,
      "text": "\"Mouse dear!"
    },
    {
      "start": 566.46,
      "end": 567.34,
      "text": "Do come back again,"
    },
    {
      "start": 567.54,
      "end": 570.38,
      "text": "and we won't talk about cats or dogs either, if you don't like them!\""
    },
    {
      "start": 571.2,
      "end": 572.08,
      "text": "When the Mouse heard this,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 572.1,
      "end": 574.16,
      "text": "it turned round and swam slowly back to her."
    },
    {
      "start": 574.88,
      "end": 576.04,
      "text": "Its face was quite pale,"
    },
    {
      "start": 576.18,
      "end": 576.7,
      "text": "with passion,"
    },
    {
      "start": 576.82,
      "end": 577.3,
      "text": "Alice thought,"
    },
    {
      "start": 577.4,
      "end": 579.34,
      "text": "and it said, in a low trembling voice,"
    },
    {
      "start": 580.28,
      "end": 581.24,
      "text": "\"Let us get to the shore,"
    },
    {
      "start": 581.38,
      "end": 582.55,
      "text": "and then I'll tell you my history,"
    },
    {
      "start": 582.8,
      "end": 585.28,
      "text": "and you'll understand why it is I hate cats and dogs.\""
    },
    {
      "start": 586.08,
      "end": 587.08,
      "text": "It was high time to go,",
      "para_break": true
    },
    {
      "start": 587.22,
      "end": 588.88,
      "text": "for the pool was getting quite crowded with"
    },
    {
      "start": 588.88,
      "end": 591.04,
      "text": "the birds and animals that had fallen into it."
    },
    {
      "start": 591.5,
      "end": 592.8,
      "text": "There were a Duck and a Dodo,"
    },
    {
      "start": 592.92,
      "end": 594.18,
      "text": "a Lory and an Eaglet,"
    },
    {
      "start": 594.24,
      "end": 595.68,
      "text": "and several other curious creatures."
    },
    {
      "start": 596.384,
      "end": 597.12,
      "text": "Alice led the way,"
    },
    {
      "start": 597.24,
      "end": 598.86,
      "text": "and the whole party swam to the shore."
    },
    {
      "start": 600.34,
      "end": 601.04,
      "text": "End of chapter two."
    }
  ]
}